{"tid":2508470,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"印度人爭相去打毒針","createTime":"2021-04-28T19:42:41.000Z","updateTime":"2021-04-28T23:41:56.000Z","uid":105798,"like":1,"dislike":8,"uniUserReply":13,"replies":[{"pid":"5ab1c0c93584a85f8908d1f41ad0d3c2276b564c","tid":2508470,"uid":105798,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-04-28T19:42:41.000Z","msg":"Indians rush for vaccines as COVID-19 death toll passes 200,000<br />\n<br />\nNEW DELHI (Reuters) - Indians struggled to register online for a mass vaccination drive set to begin at the weekend as the country&rsquo;s toll from the coronavirus surged past 200,000 on Wednesday, worsened by shortages of hospital beds and medical oxygen.<br />\n想登記都登記唔到<br />\n<br />\nThe second wave of infections has seen at least 300,000 people test positive each day for the past week, overwhelming health facilities and crematoriums and prompting an increasingly urgent response from allies overseas sending equipment.<br />\n<br />\nThe last 24 hours brought 360,960 new cases for the world&rsquo;s largest single-day total, taking India&rsquo;s tally of infections to nearly 18 million. It was also the deadliest day so far, with 3,293 fatalities carrying the toll to 201,187.<br />\n<br />\nExperts believe the official tally vastly underestimates the actual toll in a nation of 1.35 billion, however.<br />\n專家話政府計少數<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The situation is horrific, absolutely terrible ... Everyone is afraid, every single person. People are afraid that if I am talking to a person, maybe I won&rsquo;t get to talk to them tomorrow or in the near future,&rdquo; New Delhi resident Manoj Garg said.<br />\n好驚聽日會死<br />\n<br />\nDelhi state is reporting one death from COVID-19 every four minutes and ambulances have been taking the bodies of COVID-19 victims to makeshift crematorium facilities in parks and parking lots, where bodies burned on rows and rows of funeral pyres.<br />\n<br />\nMohammad Shameem, the head grave digger at Delhi&rsquo;s biggest graveyard, said: &ldquo;Earlier we had enough space here but now there is no space left. Whatever little gaps we have left, we are trying to fill them up now.&rdquo;<br />\n冇位擺屍體啦<br />\n<br />\nGenesis hospital in the Delhi suburb of Gurgaon told families to take patients away because its supplies of life-saving oxygen were depleting fast, one family said.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The hospital is trying to get fresh oxygen but we are told we have to make alternate arrangements,&rdquo; said Anjali Cerejo, whose father had been admitted but now has to try to find another bed elsewhere.<br />\n<br />\nOutside hospitals, people lined up on trolleys, and in cars and cycle rickshaws, with loved ones holding oxygen cylinders for them as they waited for a bed inside.<br />\n家屬要幫手R氧氣<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-india/indians-rush-for-covid-19-vaccines-as-death-toll-passes-200000-idUSKBN2CF0CJ\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-health-coronavirus-india%2Findians-rush-for-covid-19-vaccines-as-death-toll-passes-200000-idUSKBN2CF0CJ&d=DgCTbN7XbHZJJfbPUwNNzS2wsmw0HNSHoQ%2FRl4ZEJbA%3D&h=e8c5b8ad\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-health-coronavirus-india%2Findians-rush-for-covid-19-vaccines-as-death-toll-passes-200000-idUSKBN2CF0CJ&h=44e462d7\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-india/indians-rush-for-covid-19-vaccines-as-death-toll-passes-200000-idUSKBN2CF0CJ</a>"},{"pid":"c3dee3c04dbf6fad3427a84c0cbc87dbfbcd56b2","tid":2508470,"uid":105798,"like":3,"dislike":15,"score":-12,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-04-28T19:44:40.000Z","msg":"咁多恐懼撚既"},{"pid":"3ed99ce4f6270f8fc1c0b0cf8c6f50fd553e8745","tid":2508470,"uid":75487,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-04-28T19:45:46.000Z","msg":"針打不打 那是選擇！！<br />\n但長久下去，針是必須要打的。<br />\nyour call."},{"pid":"b